---
import "../../styles/landing.css";
import "../../styles/homepage/about-cursor.css";
import PageHeader from "../../components/PageHeader.astro";
import PcSound from "../../components/PcSound.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../../components/SiteFooter.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "");
const assetVersion = "20260413-2";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#aaaaaa" />
    <title>About — József Schaffer</title>
    <link rel="icon" href={`${base}/favicon.png?v=${assetVersion}`} />
  </head>
  <body data-about-cursor-root>
    <PageHeader base={base} showMusicPlayer />

    <div class="about-panel">
      <div class="about-panel__media">
        <img
          class="about-panel__media-image"
          src={`${base}/img/whatever_it_takes.png`}
          alt=""
          aria-hidden="true"
        />
      </div>

      <header class="about-panel__header" data-about-cursor-select>
        <h1 class="about-panel__title">Thanks for stopping by!</h1>
      </header>

      <section class="about-panel__section" data-about-cursor-select>
        <p class="about-panel__text">
          I’ve been designing and building software professionally for 15+
          years. Whether I’m evolving what already exists or creating something
          entirely new, I love figuring out what to build. I care about both
          delivery and craft.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-panel__section" data-about-cursor-select>
        <h2 class="about-panel__eyebrow">A quote I return to often</h2>
        <blockquote class="about-panel__quote">
          <p class="about-panel__text">
            <em
              >"Most of the things I am most proud of have come from just doing
              the thing</em
            >
          </p>
          <p class="about-panel__text">
            <em>Most people would rather ask questions, debate, etc</em>
          </p>
          <p class="about-panel__text">
            <em
              >Most decisions are two way doors and you are often times rewarded
              for taking the initiative"</em
            >
          </p>
          <footer class="about-panel__quote-attribution">
            —
            <a
              href="https://logank.ai"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              data-about-cursor-active>Logan Kilpatrick</a
            >
          </footer>
        </blockquote>
      </section>

      <section class="about-panel__section" data-about-cursor-select>
        <h2 class="about-panel__eyebrow">Personal tidbits about me</h2>
        <p class="about-panel__text">
          I’m originally from Hungary, happily married, a dad of three, and now
          living in southern Sweden.
        </p>
        <p class="about-panel__text">
          In my free time, I play Nintendo games, enjoy retro platformers, stay
          active, and get happily lost in pixel art.
        </p>
        <p class="about-panel__text">
          My first name, <em>József</em>, is the Hungarian version of Joseph. In
          Hungarian, it’s often shortened to <em>Józsi</em>. When pronounced in
          English, it can sound a bit like <em>Yoshi</em>. The nickname stuck,
          and that’s what most people call me. (My GitHub/scene handle is
          <em>angelday</em>. Don’t ask.)
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-panel__section" data-about-cursor-select>
        <h2 class="about-panel__title">Questions and Answers</h2>
        <dl class="about-panel__faq">
          <dt class="about-panel__question">Did you create this website?</dt>
          <dd class="about-panel__answer">
            Yes. I originally designed it in Framer, then rebuilt it using
            <a
              href="https://jamstack.org"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              data-about-cursor-active>Jamstack</a
            >
            and changed the design considerably.
          </dd>

          <dt class="about-panel__question">What tools did you use?</dt>
          <dd class="about-panel__answer">
            <a
              href="https://ghost.org"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              data-about-cursor-active>Ghost</a
            >
            as a headless CMS and
            <a
              href="https://astro.build"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              data-about-cursor-active>Astro</a
            >
            to render the site with a lot of custom enhancements. (If you’re interested,
            I wrote about the tech in a bit more depth
            <a
              href={`${base}/adding-a-cms-to-this-website/`}
              data-about-cursor-active>here</a
            >.) I also used
            <a
              href="https://www.framer.com"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              data-about-cursor-active>Framer</a
            >
            for the initial design and prototyping, Figma for some of the graphics,
            and
            <a
              href="https://www.aseprite.org"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              data-about-cursor-active>Aseprite</a
            >
            for pixel art.
          </dd>

          <dt class="about-panel__question">
            Did you make this pixel art? Or is it AI?
          </dt>
          <dd class="about-panel__answer">
            I created the pixel art above using Aseprite from a photo reference.
            You know, pixel by pixel with a lot of iterations. It’s a very
            relaxing activity!
          </dd>

          <dt class="about-panel__question">
            What’s with these weird colors and this cursor?
          </dt>
          <dd class="about-panel__answer">A nod to late-’80s CGA graphics.</dd>

          <dt class="about-panel__question">
            What video game system do you recommend buying?
          </dt>
          <dd class="about-panel__answer">
            That would be the Nintendo Switch 2, thank you for asking.
          </dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <footer class="about-panel__footer" data-about-cursor-select>
        <img
          class="about-panel__signoff-gif"
          src={`${base}/img/yoshi-cga-muted.gif`}
          alt="Yoshi"
        />
      </footer>
    </div>

    <SiteFooter />
    <PcSound />
    <div class="about-cursor" data-about-cursor aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <script is:inline type="module" define:vars={{ base }}>
      import(`${base}/js/about-cursor.js`).then((m) => m.initAboutCursor());
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
